Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows a concave area with the impression of wood like from a knob of a box, a second side shows traces of a string impression. The front shows part of an oval scarab-like impression with a circumferential line. The motif of the seal shows a sun disc and what could be part of a Sw-feather.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
